{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:41:02.444Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"ft163w3n","input":{"summary":"Upgraded the `/build` page into an ultra-premium, interactive self-service product launcher for all 'Build With GFF' tools. \n\nHere is a summary of the implementation:\n1. **Interactive Product Launcher Hero**: Customized the high-fidelity hero block to frame the GFF Build Program as a sovereign co-engineering workshop.\n2. **Continue Where You Left Off Panel**: Safely evaluates and displays real local storage states (`gff_proposal_draft_intake` and `gff_blueprint_history`) inside a premium, active session panel. Added an interactive mock-session generator allowing users to instantly simulate active blueprint and proposal drafts for testing, complete with a state-clearing option.\n3. **Interactive Path Dispatcher (Decision Guide)**: Integrated a dynamic scenario matrix addressing all requested use cases ('If you are exploring use Assessment, if you know the challenge use Talk, if you need a roadmap use Blueprint, if you need economics use ROI, if you need a proposal use Proposal Builder') where users can click on scenarios to see expected artifacts, completion times, and a clear call-to-action to launch the optimal tool.\n4. **9-Stage Enterprise Sovereign Flow Timeline**: Refined the 9 milestones (*Visitor, AI Assessment, Blueprint, Workshop, Proposal, Contract, Delivery, Operate, Expand*) into an interactive visual pipeline with progress bars, custom status indicators, and detailed artifacts per stage. Included touch-safe scroll mechanics to ensure robust mobile responsiveness.\n5. **Premium Co-Engineering Utility Suite (8 launcher cards)**: Crafted dedicated diagnostic modules for all 8 tools (*Talk to Agent, Blueprint Generator, AI Readiness Assessment, ROI Calculator, Sandbox, Proposal Builder, Marketplace, Foundry Studio*) styled with customized status tags, designated key outputs, unique inline SVG layouts, and premium hover-glow effects.\n\nValidated the solution by running a successful TypeScript type check and production build (`npm run build`), compiling perfectly with zero warnings.","verified":true}}}
